  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has issued an email alert on July 2, 2026, which may be relevant to our compliance and regulatory obligations. In Belgium and the EU, the rollout of the Markets in Crypto-Assets regulation, or MiCA, continues, with firms such as OKX and Standard Chartered securing licenses under the new framework. The European Central Bank's Frank Elderson and Christine Lagarde have also made recent public statements, with Elderson discussing the green transition and Lagarde speaking with Les Échos. Meanwhile, Poland's deadlock over MiCA implementation has left around 2,000 crypto firms without a domestic licensing route, highlighting ongoing regulatory challenges in the EU.",
